HEADWORD: Candlemas
<hw>Can"dle*mas</hw> <pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>candelm⟦ae⟧sse</ets>, <ets>candel</ets> candle +
<ets>m⟦ae⟧sse</ets> mass.]</ety> <def>The second day of February, on
which is celebrated the feast of the Purification of the Virgin Mary; --
so called because the candles for the altar or other sacred uses are
blessed on that day.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

